5000|$|The design {{principles}} of <b>ISO</b> general-purpose <b>metric</b> screw <b>threads</b> ("M" [...] series threads) are defined in international standard ISO 68-1. Each thread {{is characterized by}} its major diameter, D (Dmaj in the diagram), and its pitch, P. <b>ISO</b> <b>metric</b> <b>threads</b> consist of a symmetric V-shaped thread. In {{the plane of the}} thread axis, the flanks of the V have an angle of 60° to each other. The thread depth is 0.614 × pitch. The outermost [...] and the innermost [...] of the height H of the V-shape are cut off from the profile.|$|R
